Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
title: LI-6 Photodisintegration.

x4freetext: LI-6 Photodisintegration.
Statistical errors.
The excitation functions of reactions with a  neutron
yield  up  to energies  Eg  = 60 MeV are determined.
Besides the known maximum in the region from 7 to 17
MeV, two  broad  maxima in the energy region Eg > 19
MeV are noted on the  curve  of  dependence  of  the
total cross section of these reactions on Eg.
Real reactions with the emission of charged particles
are established and  the  energy  spectra  of  these
particles  are  determined.  relative  yield  of the
reaction are evaluated.  A substantial  contribution
(=30  mb*MeV)  of  the Li-6(g,t)He-3 reaction to the
total cross section for  the absorption of  g-quanta
by the Li-6 nucleus is registered.
The energy region of the most intense  absorption  of
gamma quanta by the Li-6 nucleus is established ( Eg
=  20  to  30  MeV,SIGMA-0   =   45   mb*MeV).   The
experimental value of the integral cross section for
the photodisintegration of the Li-6 nucleus  in  the
energy  region E-thr <= Eg <= 60 MeV does not exceed
the minimum cross section calculated by  the  dipole
sum rule (at x=0 sigma-0 = 90 mb*MeV).
Corrected by V.Varlamov, V.Mclane.
